From 2e935da9fbefd2def2f7b711a2027aa929c99374 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Zach Taylor <zctaylor.work@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 2 Jun 2026 22:25:34 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 41/48] warp.prompt: render plugin segments in the agent input
 footer too (oh-my-warp)

Pull the chip-rendering for plugin prompt segments out of PromptDisplay into a
small helper in context_chips/plugin_prompt.rs (render_plugin_chips_for_side)
and call it from BOTH:

  - PromptDisplay::render (the terminal prompt row), and
  - AgentInputFooter::render (the agent input footer chip rows).

So a plugin's warp.prompt.set([...]) is now visible in both surfaces (left and
right groups), matching where the native context chips live. No JS API change.
